This paper is about learning search strategies for classical planning problems, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper specifically focuses on policy gradient, which is a popular reinforcement learning method used in AI and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of different search algorithms, which falls under the category of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper's focus on search algorithms and optimization also makes it relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and software engineering (cs.SE).
